Package gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem

Interface SemanticItem

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<SemanticItem>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Relation, Term
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRelation, AbstractTerm, Conjunction, CoreferenceChain, Entity, Event, Expression, ImplicitRelation, Modification, Predicate, Predication
    public interface SemanticItem
extends java.lang.Comparable<SemanticItem>
    The basic interface for all textually-grounded semantic item.

    Semantic objects can be atomic, which need to further implement Term interface, or they can be complex, which need to further implement Relation interface.

    A semantic item has a type (one of potentially many semtypes), a span, and is associated with a Document. It may be normalized to an abstract concept or indicator (an ontological entity -- Ontology). It can also have a number of non-core features, maintained as key-value pairs.

    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu
    See Also:
    Term, Relation
